input:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant BaldEagle : obj
constant Cat : obj
constant Dog : obj
constant Rabbit : obj

constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Needs : obj → obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Likes : obj → obj → Prop
constant Eats : obj → obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Green BaldEagle
axiom T2 : Big Cat
axiom T3 : Rough Cat
axiom T4 : Needs Dog Cat
axiom T5 : Big Rabbit
axiom T6 : Rough Rabbit
axiom T7 : Needs Rabbit BaldEagle

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Red x ∧ Likes x Rabbit → Likes x Dog
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Dog → Likes Dog BaldEagle
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Rabbit → Eats Rabbit Cat
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Rabbit → Needs Rabbit Cat
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Big x → Needs x Rabbit
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Cat ∧ Rough x → Likes Cat Rabbit
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Eats Rabbit BaldEagle ∧ Eats BaldEagle Cat → Likes BaldEagle Dog
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Eats x Cat ∧ Likes Cat Rabbit → Eats x Dog

theorem rabbit_eats_dog : Eats Rabbit Dog :=
begin
  sorry,
end
output:
theorem rabbit_eats_dog : Eats Rabbit Dog :=
begin
  apply R8 Rabbit,
  split,
  apply R3 Rabbit,
  apply R6 Cat,
  split,
  exact T4,
  exact T3,
  apply R6 Cat,
  split,
  exact T4,
  exact T3,
end

-- The answer is True
